snippet.textDisplay:
The NFL is such a fascinating microcosm ... the Dolphins for example ... Are the Superman of NFL football. They were the first and ... STILL... only completely invincible team... In 1972 they set a precedent that they defended in 1985 against the (eventual) legendary 18-1 World Champion Chicago Bears... they did so in week 13. They could not simply allow them to go 14-0. They did this by drafting the NFL's closest analog to Clark Kent ... the indelible #13 Dan Marino in 1983... and despite only reaching the Superbowl once ... and loosing 38-16 to the DOOMSDAY that was the 1980s San Francisco 49ers ... The Dan Marino Dolphins were still still one of the mightiest, most powerful, and beloved franchises in all of existence.
This defeat of an aging and corrupted New England is just the latest installment in the heroic epic that is The Miami Dolphins. Others may have defeated Tom Brady this year.. but the Dolphins proved that perhaps ...the Patriots are not who they appeared to be all along. *Interestingly The Dolphins lost to the Patriots in that 85-86 AFC Championship game missing the chance to face those Bears again.
